  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Brain death</measure>
    <time_frame>5 days</time_frame>
    <description>Brain death defined confirmed by the mandatory criteria of the current French legislation for organ procurement including in the absence of confounding factors such as sedation, deep hypothermia, severe metabolic disorders):
clinical assessment (absence of consciousness (Glasgow score =3), absence of spontaneous respiration absence of brain stem reflexes)
paraclinical assessment: two flat and areactive electroencephalography recordings or cerebral angiography/cerebral CT scanshowing no cerebral circulation</description>
  </primary_outcome>
